Blocks.Text: This is to confirm that following course placement(s) have been offered and reserved

This enrolment will be complete subject to understanding and agreeing to all conditions of this agreement,
payment of fees and satisfactory completion of all student visa formalities.
Course Name: SIT60316 - Advanced Diploma of Hospitality Management
Students will be required to attend 20 hours per week.
Name: Sydney School of Business and Technology
Branch: Corner of York and Market St, SYDNEY, NSW

Agreed Starting Day means the day on which the course was scheduled to start, or at a later day as agreed between
Default Day means: a) the agreed starting day, if either SSBT or the student does not start on the agreed starting
day; or b) the date on which the course ceases to start if the course ceases after it starts but before being
completed or the day on which the sanction was imposed; or c) the date on which the student withdraw from
the course if the student withdraws; or d) the day on which SSBT refuses to provide the course to the student
if:1) if the student failed to pay the amount he or she is liable; or 2) the student breached his or her visa
Student Default occurs when: (i) the student does not start the course on the agreed starting day when the
course starts on that day and the student has not previously withdrawn; or (ii) the student withdraws from the
course within 28 days of agreed starting day or after the agreed starting day; or (iii) SSBT refuses to provide or
continue to provide, the course to the student because of any one or more of the following: a) That the student
failed to pay the amount he or she was liable to pay SSBT, directly or indirectly, in order to undertake the course;
b) the student breached a condition of his or her student visa; c) misbehavior by the student (refer to Deferral,
suspension and cancellation policy and procedure available on our website)
Provider Default occurs when the student has not withdrawn from the course, but i) the course does not start
on the agreed starting day; or ii) the course ceases to be provided at any time after it starts but before it is
completed; or iii) the course is not provided in full to the student because a sanction has been imposed on SSBT.
1. SSBT will pay a refund (if any) to the student, within 4 weeks, on receipt of a written claim and all supporting
